5000|$|The Roy Kirk Case: Slumlord Roy Kirk is apprehended for murdering and dismembering his {{complaining}} neighbor, Ann Hoover; examination {{also shows}} how the handcuffed and shackled Kirk hanged himself <b>in</b> the <b>police</b> <b>van</b> {{en route to the}} station.|$|R
50|$|J. S. Wilson {{provided}} {{transportation for}} Girl Guide rallies.The girls themselves were never quite sure whether they preferred to ride <b>in</b> <b>police</b> <b>vans</b> or <b>in</b> the riot truck. The former concealed them from public view, but were very hot; the latter, being cages of expanded metal, were cooler, but {{reminiscent of the}} Calcutta Zoo!In 1928, the All India Girl Guides Association joined the World Association of Girl Guides and Girl Scouts {{as one of its}} founder members. This membership was renewed in 1948 after the independence of India and its partition.|$|R
